Articles.Content: Might I suggest removing the 3D printer? It goes against the whole idea of the mod. If you want mining support, you can just use ExtraPlanetary Launchpads, now that it's compatible with OrbitalConstruction. The "shortcut" with Kethane ridiculously oversimplifies the process, and Kethane is oversimplified as it is.
i rather like the kethane 3d printer myself.
Using the 3D printer to set up an orbital station around Vall to explore Jool. Kethane miners land, dock, store, convert. I start my new base of operations there.
How does the Jump Drive work on these ships?

Might I suggest removing the 3D printer? It goes against the whole idea of the mod. If you want mining support, you can just use ExtraPlanetary Launchpads, now that it's compatible with OrbitalConstruction. The "shortcut" with Kethane ridiculously oversimplifies the process, and Kethane is oversimplified as it is.

and if we don't want exraplanetary launchpads? No i think the 3d printer should stay.

and if we don't want exraplanetary launchpads? No i think the 3d printer should stay.

I think Gary's comment bears credence, not everyone that uses orbital construction, uses EP, nor should they be forced to.

I think Gary's comment bears credence, not everyone that uses orbital construction, uses EP, nor should they be forced to.

Agreed.

Let users choose. Plain, simple..
What about balance, though? You can't just say "let users choose!" without messing up the game balancing. I'd hate for Squad to take that approach with career mode!

I don't see how mining Kethane and 3D-printing it is any easier, inherently, than using EL, mining ore, smelting it and making your parts that way.

The simplest method will always be just sending up parts from KSP, since the RocketParts are freely available, there.

Well, this is odd.

I ran into a problem after installing this mod that causes in-flight stuff to act at least "mostly normal" but when I go to the space center, I can't click on anything but the "back" button. Additionally, once I DO click that button to go to KSP's main menu screen, I can only click on the "check for updates" button. The other buttons show up, but they don't "highlight" when I mouse-over them, and just like the stuff in the Space Center screen I can't click on them. The only way for me to exit KSP in that case is to hit Ctrl-Alt-Del, bring up the Task Manager, go to the "processes" tab, right click on KSP.exe and hit "End Task".

The end result isn't a "Crash" per se. but I almost wish it was, because then at least I would have a crash report to look thru.

I'm not absolutely sure if this bug is due to too many mods installed, a mod conflict , or an actual bug in this Orbital Construction mod.

However, I have gotten it to happen twice in a row (and needed to restart KSP each time of course).

Here's how I got it to happen.

You will need at least 3 addons that have plugins: this mod, the Extraplanetary Launchpads mod (E.L. mod for short), and Kethane 0.7.5

Setup:

You will need one "Orbital Shipyard" in orbit around Kerbin (mine is in a 250k x 250k 0Ã‚Â° orbit)

An Orbital Shipyard is a vessel that has all of these parts:

  • at least 1 pod and/or 1 probe core
  • Batteries with some combination of Solar Panels and/or RTGs to keep them charged
  • EXACTLY ONE SpaceDock part
  • one or more RocketParts containers (I used 4 of the "medium" sized HexCans included in the E.L. mod)

Now build a "Launchpad" ship that includes everything on this list:

  • at least 1 pod and/or 1 probe core
  • Batteries with some combination of Solar Panels and/or RTGs to keep them charged
  • The "Runway" part from the E.L. mod
  • A Kethane drill, Kethane tank, and Kethane converter
  • At least one tank for each of the "stock" resources except for IntakeAir (LiquidFuel+Oxidizer, MonoPropellant, and XenonGas)
  • EXACTLY ONE SpaceBuilt part.

To make building the lander-section of the "Launchpad" easier, you only need to make it capable of landing on Minmus, or any other planet/moon with similarly low gravity and no atmosphere (Minmus just happens to be the closest planet or moon to Kerbin that meets those criteria)

Replicating the problem:

  1. Make sure that your "Orbital Shipyard" ship has a small amount of RocketParts stored. More than 0, but not enough to build the "Launchpad" ship.
  2. Launch the "Launchpad" ship from the VAB (or SPH if you built it there)
  3. (pretend to) Realize that you don't have enough RocketParts at the Orbital Shipyard to build the Launchpad there.
  4. Pause the game, but Instead of Reverting the flight to the VAB (/SPH), go to the Space Center.
  5. You should now not be able to click on any of the buildings in the Space Center view. Moving the camera should work as it normally does, but you should only be able to click on the "Back" button in the lower-right hand corner.
  6. Click the "Back" button in the Space Center view.
  7. You should now be on the Main Menu screen. However, you will not be able to click on any of the "New Game" "Load Game" "Settings" "Credits" "SpacePort" or even the "Quit" button. However, you SHOULD be able to click on the "Check For Updates" button in the lower-left hand corner. At this point the only way to exit the game is to kill the KSP.exe process.

I don't know what causes this specific problem, but I have some interesting data from the debug console (Alt+F2) that seems like it's related to the effects I observed.

With the multiple input and output resources, the format of the KethaneConverter node has changed.

Here's a sample (EL smelter):


    MODULE {
        name = KethaneConverter
        InputRates {
            Ore = 3
            ElectricCharge = 10
        }
        OutputRatios {
            // From http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iron_ore
            // Stage One: 3 Fe2O3 + CO Ã¢â€ â€™ 2 Fe3O4 + CO2
            // Stage Two: Fe3O4 + CO Ã¢â€ â€™ 3 FeO + CO2
            // Stage Three: FeO + CO Ã¢â€ â€™ Fe + CO2
            //
            // Until parts can be made, ignore CO/CO2.
            //
            // So 3Fe2O3 + 9CO Ã¢â€ â€™ 6Fe + 9CO2, Fe = 55.845, O = 15.999 which
            // means 479.061g of ore will produce 335.070g of iron. Kethane
            // takes care of the relative densities for us, thus the ratio is
            // just 355.07/479.061.
            Metal = 0.699431
        }
    }

right, so following that logic i update the part.cfg in the OC_3DPrinter folder.

From :

MODULE

{

name = KethaneConverter

SourceResource = Kethane

TargetResource = RocketParts

ConversionEfficiency = 0.99

SourceConsumption = 500

PowerConsumption = 12

}

to :

MODULE

{

name = KethaneConverter

InputRates

{

Kethane = 500

ElectricCharge = 12

}

OutputRatios

{

RocketParts = 0.99

}

}

so that did the trick, thanks taniwha.
